caption: Great food and service
Line was pretty long. The best time to stand on line is a little after 12 that is when the rush dies down. Food was pretty good not the best. But its a good vibe.
Soooo good
Very good gumbo and po-boys. Prices were reasonable.great service.

Love us some Mena’s. The best home fries I’ve tasted thus far. The pancakes and french toast you must try. The staff is friendly and the service is always great. During city events they will get crowded and a line will form. But it’s worth the wait.
Ordered chili cheese fries & a burger . 10/10 , & definitely the best chili cheese fries I ever had !

If I was rating the food alone I may have gone with three stars.  Perhaps I just got there on a bad day as people had raved about the food.  But the Fried shrimp and french fries, while plentiful, had the taste of cooked in old oil.  If anything, I could only eat a quarter of the plate.  I will say, if you order a salad, definitely go for their home made dressing.  It's an Italian style that had the perfect amount of herbs and spices.  The service is also wonderful.  The service and personalities was like walking into a 1960s small town diner.  Laid back and made you feel like you were a regular.

The staff is really sweet and the food is delicious. I recommend the poor boys full dressed. The prices for French quarter were great too. I'm sure they get busy sometimes, we were very lucky to not have a wait.
Seriously you have to try this place! Every time I come NOLA this place is a must. Great breakfast and lunch and if it’s cold the hot chocolate is delicious. LOVE IT HERE
Great breakfast, huge portions, and good prices.
Friendly staff and good food the side salad came on a saucer dish which was odd but over all good.
Shrimp Poboy. You have to get it.
Best Chicken friend steak ! Made a visit from Georgia and was not disappointed!
Very good food and service!

Great breakfast!

Great food, excellent service
Great fried chicken!

Mena'sPalace sure don't look like much..but don't judge a restaurant on it's  exterior looks.  We had dinner on the curb because of Covid Capicity regulations. Their specials change from day to day. Today was red beans and rice with fried chicken. The beans and rice was easily enough to feed two. The fried chicken was absolutely delicious. I love man sized portions but this pushed my ability to clean my plate. Wonderful  dining experience  and super nice staff made this a very memorable meal.
First place I've enjoyed a glass of ouzo since i was in Greece. Their food is great, they make their home fries the right way. Loved it
Staff is super friendly, food is amazing. Great prices, fast service.

Mena’s is a must when we’re in the Quarter! It’s certainly not fancy, but it’s clean and comfortable. Their menus are paper and written in a chalkboard. Waitresses are friendly and efficient. Miss Ellie, the owner, is always welcoming. I’ve carried out from there so often that I’m greeted like an old friend. Prices are quite reasonable and portions are plentiful. And the food is absolutely delicious!
Breakfast was horrible..egg cooked hard pancakes was too dry and bacon was not crispy looked old..paid for 2 large OJ gave us 2 8oz cups..very disappointed

(Translated by Google) Served only lunch at 12 no indication. Vegetarian options at lunch are completely absent. Is this really up to date?  (Original) Serviert um 12 nur noch Lunch, kein Hinweis darauf. Vegetarische Optionen beim Lunch fehlen gänzlich. Ist dies wirklich zeitgemäß?
Great breakfast

My girlfriends and I went to Mena’s Palace on Mardi Gras morning, we were looking for some good breakfast food. Although we had to wait in line outside the host was very attentive and continued to update us with the wait status. When we sat down the server named Chelsea was amazing. She was very sweet and catering. The food was amazing and the peach mimosa that Chelsea suggested was incredible. The service and the hospitality was so great that we decided to go back again today and specifically asked and waited to be served by Chelsea, and the lunch menu was just as great. I would definitely recommend this place to anyone that wants great service and good home style food. Check out Chelsea because she was great.
Affordable good tasting food.
It was ok
Great spot for lunch!
We went here nearly every morning whilst on holiday. Staff were so friendly & helpful. Their French toast and bacon; my god, I still dream about it. Would give more stars if possible!
What's not to love about that place!!!!
Great service! The place is small but the food is good. I enjoyed the catfish and grits.

Ordered the Grilled Chicken plate which comes with a baked potato and side salad, I asked for a Cesar Salad as my side salad but I got what ever they decided to give me, also asked them to add cheese to my baked potato (which normally comes with just butter and sour cream), needless to say I got a DRY potato with only cheese thrown on top of it, no butter or sour cream. Thank you for paying attention to what your customers ask and pay for!
The food and service was so great that we went two days in a row. And if there’s a wait to get in, it’s worth it!!!
Absolutely delightful staff and delicious food. A wonderful place to start your day!
We happened upon Mena’s on our last day in New Orleans. The service and did is Amazing. Over the years we have eaten at many places in NOLA, Mena’s is now at the top of the list!

My wife had the Cajun Tasso omelet and loved it. I had the Andouille sausage omelet and loved it. We shared a hot cake and loved it. Great coffee. Very, very reasonable pricing for the Quarter ... Make this your breakfast stop at least once, great little establishment with great service.
Great breakfast would visit again.

This place was amazing! Originally we were standing in line at Dazy Dukes but one quick glance at the menu, I knew we should try Menas!  What amazing food and quick service. If you have to wait, it's totally worth it!  The bread for the poboy is phenomenal! We had the hot roast beef. Loved it so much we also ordered one to take with us!
Excellent. Ordered the shrimp poboy. The shrimp were perfectly seasoned and perfectly cooked. One of the best I e had in a long time. Highly recommended.
Mr. Leo has been pouring Ouzo for over 44 years!

This place is most definitely open!! We have been here twice on our visit to New Orleans this Christmas season and will most likely be back a third time & of course every time we come back into town!!  We enjoyed their breakfast which they serve until noon! I’m coming back for their bread pudding & lunch!  Their andouille sausage omelet is amazing! We absolutely love their breakfast potatoes!  Let me tell you about their bacon! Yummy!  What originally brought me here was a picture of their bacon & hot cakes!! They lived up to the pictures!!  You come in and seat yourself! We enjoyed all of our visits!  Make sure you try a drink from their bar!! They have a lemon cello mimosas drink!!

Adorable corner restaurant/diner! Came for a simple breakfast, and loved it. High quality ingredients, delicious potatoes and grits and eggs. Fast and friendly service, no wait at 9am on a Sunday. Highly recommend for a simple quality breakfast.

Husband and I had breakfast here. We got our omelets & one plate with 3 pieces of unbutered rye toast. I ordered dry rye and my husband ordered buttered rye. We called the waitress over to let her know that my husband didn't get his toast. She said breakfast comes with only 1 slice. We got 1 slice and a 1/2 of one slice. She never said that toast doesn't come buttered when we ordered. So taken back that I did not say anymore. Food was good but would not come back here.
Has thing that are different from other stores.

When I go to New Orleans my meal metric is whether the food is worth the caloric intake or not (after all you are in New Orleans).  Mena’s fell short of my metric on this visit and I place it in the average category.  I had the fried oysters which were plump and not overly breaded.  They also had a pleasant flavor.  However, the accompanying salad was merely a pile of iceberg lettuce.  The french fries tasted like soggy cardboard and not worth the effort.  Judging my the lines this place is very popular, however with so many other dining options you may want to explore elsewhere.  In fairness, my sample was only one all fried food dish so maybe its the other options that bring in the lines.
Delicious food.

Three of us were in town for a week and came back again and again—wound up having breakfast here four times! The French toast was cooked perfectly every time; omelettes and such were all fine. The wait can be a little long at time so check the Google busy meter at the bottom of the Google maps entry to see when you should time your visit. Food. Not. That. Good

I just left this place very disappointed.  1- the person who sat next to me arrived after me and their order was taken before me. Not good.  2- I first asked for coffee but my sever forgot. When the person next to received their coffee before me, my sever noticed and finally came over to take my food order and attempted to claim that this person’s server mistakenly gave her my coffee. I told her no, her entire order was taken. She should have admitted she forgot my coffee. Not good.  3- I ordered the pancakes with a side of eggs over medium. The pancakes tasted like they came out of a box mix. They were flavorless. I had to pay the same amount for them despite ordering them without the meat side that they come with. Not good.  4- the eggs “over medium” were very runny. Not good.  5- they don’t have real maple syrup or honey. Instead they give you something called “Smucker’s Breakfast Syrup” and the first two ingredients are corn syrup and high fructose corn syrup. Yikes. Not good.  This along with the coffee I ordered wasn’t worth the $17.20 I paid. Go elsewhere for better service and food.
